  <!-- Begin PyXDG -->
  <sect2 id="pyxdg" xreflabel="PyXDG-&pyxdg-version;">

    <title>PyXDG-&pyxdg-version;</title>

    <indexterm zone="pyxdg">
      <primary sortas="a-PyXDG">PyXDG</primary>
    </indexterm>

    <sect3 role="package">
      <title>Introduction to PyXDG Module</title>

      <para>
        <application>PyXDG</application> is a <application>Python</application>
        library to access freedesktop.org standards.
      </para>

      &lfs130_checked;

      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Package Information</bridgehead>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&pyxdg-download-http;"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Download (FTP): <ulink url="&pyxdg-download-ftp;"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Download MD5 sum: &pyxdg-md5sum;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Download size: &pyxdg-size;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Estimated disk space required: &pyxdg-buildsize;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Estimated build time: &pyxdg-time;
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Additional Downloads</bridgehead>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Required patch: <ulink url="&patch-root;/pyxdg-&pyxdg-version;-python3_14-fixes-1.patch"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">PyXDG Dependencies</bridgehead>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect5">Optional (for testing)</bridgehead>
      <para role="optional">
        <xref linkend="pytest"/> and
        <xref linkend="shared-mime-info"/>
      </para>

    </sect3>

    <sect3 role="installation">
      <title>Installation of PyXDG</title>

      <para>
        First, fix several problems caused by Python 3.14:
      </para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">patch -Np1 -i ../pyxdg-&pyxdg-version;-python3_14-fixes-1.patch</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        Build the module:
      </para>

&build-wheel;

       <para>
         Install the module as the &root; user:
       </para>

<screen role='root'><userinput>&install-wheel; pyxdg</userinput></screen>

       <para>
         To test the results, issue: <command>pytest</command>. Note that two
         tests, <filename>MimeTest::test_get_type</filename> and
         <filename>MimeTest::test_get_type2</filename>, are known to fail due
         to small differences in MIME types from the recent versions of the
         shared-mime-info package.
       </para>

    </sect3>

